The paper discusses a neural architecture for question answering using a knowledge graph and web corpus. This falls under the intersection of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), which are covered by the sub-categories cs.CL and cs.IR. The use of convolutional networks and latent variables suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are covered by cs.AI and cs.LG. Finally, the incorporation of a knowledge graph suggests a focus on databases, covered by cs.DB.
